
<!--

18. Other Tricks:  	  
  18.7 Margin and auto
  
    Can centre an item within a container provided it has a
	width by:
	
	margin-left: auto;
	margin-right: auto;

19. HTML and CSS Summary
  19.1 HTML: 
    - for content only
	- HTML5 has semantic meanings to many elements
	- different browswers may render elements differently
	by default
	- web browser parses HTML, styles elements, and renders
	them to the screen

  19.2 CSS:
    - tells the brower how to render the html elements
	- almost all elements have: content, padding, borders,
	margins, and properties like position, height/width,
	background-color, color, etc.
	- by referencing (in increasing specificity) elements,
	classes, and ids, we are able to make elements display
	as we like

20. Publishing a Webpage Online  
   - most of the time, should have a public_html folder
   - the homepage is by default called index.html
   - can create directories within the site and link around

21. Intro to JavaScript
   - JavaScript is a scripting language that runs on the user's
   end
   - Highly event-driven: when a page is loaded, when a button
   is clicked, etc.
   - Has variables, functions, and "classes" (not really object
   oriented)
   - Variable names and types are more relaxed
   - Browser may forgive syntax errors (missing semi-colons, etc.)
   - When it fails, may be hard to detect: stuff just doesn't load
   or change 


-->

